Root Account: Is the admin/super user of the Linux system, can have all access to all files and system
User Account: Regular user who can have limited access on linux system 

Root directory ( '/' ) : Is the very first directory in the linux system
Root home ('/root') : Is the home directory of root user (ex: 275868, thotaa) 

Command to change the password:
Root account : passwd username --> passwd root

