Command prompt:
A Command prompt, also referred as a prompt, which is a short text at the begining of the command line followed by a prompt symbol on a command line interface.
Ex: [arjun@MYLinuxVM ~]$
    # - root commond prompt symbol
    $ - user commond prompt symbol

Root command prommpt : [root@MyLinuxVM ~]#
User command prompt: [arjun@MYLinuxVM ~]$
Note: If lost commond prompt , user 'cntrl+c' to bring back
